LDAP

Find enabled/disabled 

ldapsearch -x -H 'ldap://10.10.10.100' -D 'SVC_TGS' -w 'GPPstillStandingStrong2k18' -b "dc=active,dc=htb" -s sub "(&(objectCategory=person)(objectClass=user)(! (useraccountcontrol:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=2)))" samaccountname | grep sAMAccountName

ldapsearch: Command-line tool to query LDAP directories.
-x: Use simple authentication.
-H 'ldap://10.10.10.100': Connect to the LDAP server at 10.10.10.100.
-D 'SVC_TGS': Bind (authenticate) as the user SVC_TGS.
-w 'GPPstillStandingStrong2k18': Use this password for authentication.
-b "dc=active,dc=htb": Set the search base to the domain "active.htb".
-s sub: Search the entire subtree.
"(&(objectCategory=person)(objectClass=user)(!(useraccountcontrol:1.2.840.113556.1.4.803:=2)))": LDAP filter for objects that are:
Category: person
Class: user
NOT disabled (the last part excludes disabled accounts)
samaccountname: Only return the samaccountname attribute (the username).

Windows uses a bitmask for this, therefore we must always use the 2 (ACCOUNTDISABLE) value, and the
! operator when looking for enabled accounts.
















